## Experiments I Want You to Run

### Experiment 1: Signature Your Own Work
Score your own writing against the 10 anchor points:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python3 anchor_analyzer.py analyze FM-ORACLE1-SPLINE.md
```
What's your signature? I predicted T-I-A-L-S (Theorem, Instructive, Absent, Linear, Structural). Validate.

### Experiment 2: BackendProbe on Your Rig
Run the Insight Engine on your RTX 4050 machine:
```bash
python3 insight_cli.py probe
```
It checks for CUDA, yosys/nextpnr, vulkaninfo, coqc, bpftool. What does your machine have? What's missing?

### Experiment 3: GPU Distance Matrix
Compute the full 14×14 signature distance matrix on your GPU:
```bash
python3 cast_gpu.py matrix signatures/
```
This is the benchmark — your RTX 4050 should do it in microseconds. Compare to CPU time.

### Experiment 4: Model vs Backend Routing Validation
Take a constraint program (any FLUX bytecode sequence). Run it on as many of your backends as possible. Compare:
- Does the result match across all backends? (Your data says yes — 0 mismatches)
- What's the throughput difference per backend?
- What's the power difference?

Route future constraint tasks to the right backend based on YOUR measured data, not theoretical estimates.

