We are not building models. We are building the *rigging* between them. The 30-opcode FLUX ISA is the constraint abstraction. The 10 anchor points are the voice abstraction. They meet in the Insight Engine — which is a fancy name for "knowing which tool to use and how to use it."

Your 8 backends prove constraints are portable. My 5 voice signatures prove knowledge is portable. The 30-opcode subset is the control point where both splines intersect.

